1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with joint source-channel coding, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper involves video compression and replication, which is a common application in multimedia. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system and associated strategies for joint source-channel coding and transmission control, which is a topic in systems and control. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper involves transmission of data over a channel, which is a topic in networking and internet architecture. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes algorithms for joint source-channel coding, which is a topic in data structures and algorithms.
